;
;ROOMS (including Haven, Catacombs Extension and Heroes Hill ext.)
;
NUMBER 2575
NAME Top of Rise
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
REGION 11
*DESCRIPTION_START SPRING
A rutted road leads into a ramshackle town of crude dwellings from this
point. Nestled protectively in the cradle of the circular mountain range
the small town serves as the home base for Captain Bloodheart's Pirates.
The town is split into two sections, one alive with activity, the other
dark and ominous filled with ruined buildings. From behind you can hear
the muted sounds of the jungle emanating along a path which leads into
the heart of the leafy domain. A battered wooden sign sits by the edge
of the road. To the north and east you can see the imposing mountains
that ring most of the island. The towering, barren peaks seem to increase
the isolation of the tiny atoll.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT D 2576
ITEM 1 204 ADJ1=21 ADJ2=355
ITEM 2 80 VAL2=2622
MONSTER_GROUP 94
CALL 83
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 1
Scrawled, in blood, on the sign is;
            CORSAIR'S HAVEN
    If pirate ye not be, pass no further.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
NUMBER 2576
NAME Haven, intersection
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
REGION 11
*DESCRIPTION_START SPRING
Coming down over a crest the town can be more easily viewed now. Consisting
of mainly wooden buildings, in obvious need of repair, and many crumbled
stone dwellings, Haven is a testament to the sloth of its inhabitants. From
this point the road continues north, into the center of the town, which
seems more active than the silent ruins that lie past a pile of rubble to
the east. Far beyond the rubble the road seems to end at a cemetery of sorts.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT U 2575
EXIT N 2623
ITEM 0 213 VAL2=2577
MONSTER_GROUP 94
CALL 83
IFVERB LISTEN -1
    ECHO PLAYER Your ears pick up the sound of raucous voices coming from the north.
ENDIF
IFVERB SMELL -1
  ECHO PLAYER The faint smell of some unwholesome, sickly odor lies to the east.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 2577
NAME Haven, ruins
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
REGION 11
*DESCRIPTION_START SPRING
Fire scorched, crumbling buildings of stone stand like silent monuments to a
bygone era along this cracked and weed-infested road. A soft breeze brings
the sound of life from the northwest, yet the noise seems to die as soon as
it reaches this still spot.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 2578
ITEM 0 213 VAL2=2576
MONSTER_GROUP 95
IFVERB SMELL -1
  ECHO PLAYER The smell of rot and decay is stronger here.
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER Your ears strain to hear any noise, but the only thing you hear is your own strained breathing.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 2578
NAME Haven, ruins
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
REGION 11
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Large piles of rubble press against the broken road from either side of it.
The rubble seems alive with a foul miasma of sickness and rot. The road
forks around a stone building that is surprisingly enough still in good
condition. The building is of ornate design, perhaps being the former
residence of someone important, and has withstood the trials of the years
to remain standing. A small cobblestone path winds its way past the
sickly crab grass of the house's front lawn to a sturdy looking door.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 2577
EXIT NE 2581
EXIT SE 2580
ITEM 0 80 ADJ1=294 VAL2=2579
MONSTER_GROUP 95
;
NUMBER 2579
NAME Haven, mansion door
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
REGION 11
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Brooding malovelence and sickness emanate from the dark house before you.
Its oppressive silence and darkness hanging before you with crushing weight.
A single, stout oaken door guards the mysteries contained within the house.
Behind you the sickly, yellow grass of the front lawn brings the stench of
death and decay to your nostrils...
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 80 ADJ1=294 VAL2=2578
ITEM 1 943 ADJ1=997 ADJ2=447 VAL1=5000
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
Taking a closer look at the door you notice several faint scratch marks set
into the door, as if someone, or something, had attempted entry. Dried blood
is also present in the marks, and in many spots, the broken fingernails of
those who attempted entry.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB KNOCK 1
  ECHO ALL The door glows brightly, illuminating all in a brilliant white light. When the light fades you see the flickering image of a man's head floating in the center of the door. Ancient and powerful eyes gaze at you before speaking, "Begone you plague-ridden scum! None may enter my dwelling!" After this speech the head flickers and fades.
ENDIF
IFVERB SEARCH -1
  ECHO PLAYER As you look about the area you get the faint impression that you are being watched, yet when you look closer you don't see any signs of anyone.
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 2580
NAME Haven, street
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
REGION 11
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Large piles of rubble block any further passage to the south here. It seems
as if the prior citizens of Haven made some effort to move all of the rubble
to this spot, before they all succumbed. The dark shape of a still-standing
house looms over you to the north.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NW 2578
MONSTER_GROUP 95
;
NUMBER 2581
NAME Haven, street
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
REGION 11
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The eerie silence of this section of town is punctuated, sporadically, by
the sounds of small claws scratching against rocks. The noises seem to be
coming from the large piles of rubble that decorate either side of the
street. To the east, atop a small knoll is what seems to be an imposing
mausoleum, sitting on top of the hill like a dark, brooding sentinel.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT SW 2578
EXIT E 2583
ITEM 0 213 VAL2=2582
MONSTER_GROUP 95
;
NUMBER 2582
NAME Ruined House, interior
INDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
REGION 11
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The stone floor of this former dwelling has remained remarkably free of
debris. The walls and ceiling have long since collapsed and lie scattered
in piles along the sides of the house. Intriguingly enough, painted, in
the center of the floor is a stylish representation of a Golden Tiger.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 213 VAL2=2581
;
NUMBER 2583
NAME Cemetery, Gate
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
REGION 11
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A rusted iron fence sways precariously around the cemetery of Haven. Gazing
through the rusted-shut gate you can see that there is an abundance of
graves. Obviously something caused many deaths in Haven's past. The foul
stench of rotting corpses is brought through the gate on a mild breeze,
nearly making you retch. Three skeletons swing back and forth on the wind,
hung from the gate by their necks.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 2581
ITEM 0 68 VAL1=5000 VAL2=2584 CLOSED LOCKED
ITEM 1 390
ITEM 2 390
ITEM 3 390
MONSTER_GROUP 95
VARIABLE skeleton
IFENTRY
 IFITEM 0 OPEN
   ECHO PLAYER The rusted gate swings creakingly back and forth in the breeze, opened by some unseen force.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB GO 0
  IFVAR skeleton ! 2
   CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You can hear the skeletons laughing in your head, "Answer our riddle you haven't!"
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB TOUCH 1
 IFVAR skeleton ! 2
  ECHO ALL The skeleton shivers with delight and then says, "Small and unseen am I."
ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB TOUCH 2
 IFVAR skeleton ! 2
  ECHO ALL The skeleton shivers with delight and then says, "Kings and kingdoms I lay to waste."
ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB TOUCH 3
 IFVAR skeleton ! 2
  ECHO ALL The skeleton shivers with delight and then says, "My only harvest is death."
ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY plague
 IFVAR skeleton ! 2
  ECHO ALL All of the skeleton's begin roaring with anger, shouting, "No fair! No Fair! Your flesh we wanted to feast upon!"
  ECHO ALL You hear the gate click open!
  OPEN 0
  EQUAL SKELETON 2
 ENDIF
ENDIF
