OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
REGION 11
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Surrounded on all sides by strangely vibrant flowerbeds, that provide a
sharp contrast to the dark marble exterior, is a mausoleum with an arch
providing entry. Written above the arch, in the old script popular almost
500 years ago, is, "Cheydalin, trusted friend, forgive me my trespass."
*DESCRIPTION_END
