NUMBER 2587
NAME Cemetery, graves
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
REGION 11
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Weathered headstones, most of them cracked and pitted, thrust from the
blackened ground like the rotting teeth of a giant. Sickly yellow
grass covers the face of most of the stones, making the writing upon them
hard to read. The jumbled arrangement of the numerous graves, and the
decided lack of care for them, makes it hard to move through this portion
of the cemetery.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 2584
EXIT SE 2588
ITEM 0 1907 ADJ1=584
MONSTER_GROUP 95
VARIABLE sharkey
VARIABLE sharkey1
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
You can barely make out some child-like scrawls across the face of this
particular headstone.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 0
              OLD SHARKEY
                ? - 957

  "His doom, the demon he couldn't get enough of."
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB SMELL -1
  ECHO PLAYER The smell of decaying flesh seems to seep from the ground all around you, clogging your nostrils with its foul miasma.
  ECHO OTHERS %N gags as %s inhales.
ENDIF
IFVERB SEARCH -1
  ECHO PLAYER One headstone grabs your attention, mainly because it isn't as grass-covered as the rest.
ENDIF
IFSAY rum
  ADD sharkey 1
   IFVAR sharkey = 1
     ECHO ALL A faint mocking laughter drifts through the cemetery after %N intones the word.
   ENDIF
