NUMBER 2588
NAME Cemetery, withered tree
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
REGION 11
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Stretching its twisted limbs across the dark expanse of the far corner of
the cemetery is a large, withered oak tree. The tree's vitality has long
since been drained by whatever insidious poison is present in the ground
of this unholy place. A few shattered headstones lie in crumbling pieces
around the tree, the graves they marked lost in the profusion of yellow
grass that covers the ground.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NW 2587
ITEM 0 229 ADJ1=1156
MONSTER_GROUP 95
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
Long, dark stains mar the trunk of the dead tree.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFENTRY
 IFITEM 1
  ECHO PLAYER You notice that a section of earth has been turned up, exposing a grave.
 ENDIF
  RANDOM dummy1 1 100 0
    IFVAR dummy1 => 90
      SETEVENT 60 1 ALWAYS
      CONTEVENT 60
      ECHO PLAYER Your movements become slowed and time seems to freeze around you. A shimmering glow surrounds the tree and dark apparitions rise from the ground. As you watch intently a drama from the past is played out...
      ECHO OTHERS %N stops and stares, wide-eyed at the tree, at something that you can't see..
      SETEVENT 61 2 ALWAYS
      CONTEVENT 61
      ECHO PLAYER The apparitions assume the guise of bloodthirsty buccaners surrounding a slowly swaying figure that is hanging from the tree, a rope tied around its neck...
      SETEVENT 62 2 ALWAYS
      CONTEVENT
      ECHO PLAYER With a chillingly determined movement, the head of one of the pirates turns to gaze directly at you. Its hollow eye sockets burn red as it speaks with a voice from beyond time, and beyond life, "Cross Bloodheart...and pay the price.", the apparitions then sink back into the ground and you feel time resume its natural course.
      ECHO OTHERS %N gasps and turns pale.
    ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB TOUCH 0
  IFVAR SKILL17 => 5
    ECHO PLAYER The tree is quite dead, but there are some faint resonances of the evil and horror that it witnessed in life.
    ECHO OTHERS %N sighs sadly as %s touches the tree.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
