NUMBER 2591
NAME Demon Ship, main deck
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Flickering fingers of flame caper madly along the blood-stained wood of
this hellish ship. Crimson rivers of blood flow from the pores of the
wood making for treacherous footing. In the center of deck is a mast made
from the molded bones of the ships victims. Extending from this foul mast
are thin strings that resemble dried intestines. The intestines snap in
the wind, straining against the pulling force of the large sails that power
the ship. A closer glance at the sails confirms that they are made from
the sewn-together skin of various humanoids. A single gangplank leads back
to the docks of Corsair's Haven and sanity...
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 2593
EXIT E 2595
ITEM 0 1149
EXTEND 0 made from molded bones
MONSTER_GROUP 101
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The horrid mast seems to sweat blood from its shiny exterior.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB CLIMB 0
  DISBAND
    CLEARVERB
     RANDOM dummy3 1 100 0
     ADD dummy3 AGI
       IFVAR dummy3 => 170
        ECHO PLAYER Somehow you manage to find some handholds on the bloody mast and you clamber up towards the crow's nest...
        ECHO OTHERS %N manages to clamber up the bloody mast, soon disappearing out of reach.
        MOVE 2592
        AFFECT 2592
        ECHO OTHERS %N clambers into the crow's nest.
        AFFECT 2591
        ELSE
        ECHO PLAYER You can't find any handholds and quickly slide back down to the deck along the bloody mast.
        ECHO OTHERS %N can't find any handholds and quickly slides back down onto the deck.
        POSITION LAY
       ENDIF
     EQUAL ROUNDTIME 10
ENDIF
IFVERB GO 1
  CLEARVERB
    MOVEGROUP 2590
    ECHO GROUP %N leads you down the gangplank
    ECHO OTHER GROUP %P goes down the gangplank.
    AFFECT 2590
    ECHO OTHER GROUP %P comes scurrying off the black ship.
    AFFECT 2591
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER The continous roar of hellish fires assaults your eardrums with an evil rhythm.
  ECHO OTHERS %N winces and puts %h hands over %h ears.
ENDIF
IFVERB SMELL -1
 IFVAR RAC ! 7
  ECHO PLAYER The nauseating stench of boiling blood fills your nostrils and makes the bile rise in your throat.
  ECHO OTHERS %N looks like %s is going to lose breakfast over the rail.
 ENDIF
 IFVAR RAC = 7
   ECHO PLAYER Your nose filters recognize the smell as that of humanoid blood being subjected to extreme temperatures.
   ECHO OTHERS %N clinically sniffs the air.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
