NUMBER 2592
NAME Demon Ship, crow's nest
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Rigging, made from human intestines, stretches out in all directions from
this crows nest. The actual nest consists of several joined skulls with,
appropriately enough, crows eyes placed into their empty eye sockets. The
bone mast extends upwards, through the center of the skull floor, for a few
feet before it ends. A black pennant snaps in the wind at the top of the
mast. Upon the mast is sewn the symbol of Captain Bloodheart, a single
human heart with blood dripping from it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 352
ITEM 1 1149
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The crow eye, placed in the eye socket of the skull, seems to meet your
gaze with an intensity that sends shivers across your body.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB CLIMB 1
  DISBAND
   CLEARVERB
     ECHO PLAYER You easily slide down the mast to the deck.
     ECHO OTHERS %N slides down the mast to the deck.
     MOVE 2591
     AFFECT 2591
     ECHO OTHERS %N slides down the mast.
     AFFECT 2592
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER The slow shifting of the crows eyes is the only noise that can be heard over the shrieking wind.
  ECHO OTHERS %N shudders and looks anywhere but at the skulls.
ENDIF
IFENTRY
  RANDOM dummy4 1 20 0
    IFVAR dummy4 => 18
      ECHO ALL All of the skulls start chattering at once, "Avast! Boarders sighted!", as %N climbs into view.
      AFFECT 2591
      ECHO ALL You hear the chattering of skulls from above.
      AFFECT 2593
      ECHO ALL You hear the chattering of skulls from above.
      AFFECT 2595
      ECHO ALL YOu hear the chattering of skulls from above.
    ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 2593
NAME Demon Ship, foredeck
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The burning railings of the horrid ship curve inwards until they meet at
the figurehead here. The stiff breeze from the harbor whips the magical
flames into a frenzy causing them to form into miniature elementals that
dance macabrely across the deck. High above, the sails of humanoid skin
flutter bringing the stench of rotting flesh down to you. The figurehead
is out of reach, but you can see that it is designed to look like a nude
female aelfen, her body shredded by thorns and her eyes weeping tears of
blood. A large opening in the deck leads down.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 2591
EXIT D 2594
MONSTER_GROUP 101
IFENTRY
  RANDOM dummy3 1 100 0
   IFVAR dummy3 => 85
     ECHO PLAYER Your eyes are drawn to the figurehead of the ship, which seems to gaze directly at you and mouth, "Eternal pain and damnation are mine...", while her eyes bleed copiously.
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 2594
NAME Demon Ship, hold
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The only part of the ship untouched by flames is this cargo hold. Instead
an icy cold grips your body, brought on by the horrid crates which are
stacked along the walls of the room. The crates seem to move slightly,
whether their movement is caused by the motion of the ship of some other
force is not readily apparent...
