    Brama 17, 1015:
        "Those accursed Faydians have driven me from my own town! I will
         go to sea and plot my revenge, then I will strike with the fury
         of a hurricane."

    Dretmar 3, 1015:
        "The men rumble with mutiny, yet my desire for revenge upon Fayd
        still burns brightly within my heart."

    Dretmar 12, 1015:
        "He came again last night, in my fevered dreams. He promises to
        aid me in my plans against Fayd. His words are wise, I think that
	I may accept his aid, even though my men cross themselves like
        foolish spaewives when I mention my dreams."

    Dretmar 15, 1015:
        "It is done...and I am pleased even though I now know that I have
        dealt with a demon. I accepted the aid which the man from my
        dreams has offered and he shed his guise and assumed the shape of
        the demon he truly is. I accept this calmly, for I know that he
        will help see my plans to fruition. Even now the demon 'converts'
        those of my men who still rebell against my wishes. I must confess
        that their screams send a delicious chill through my body."

     Abra 7, 1016:
        "I am a demon now, the process is done. I have slaked my thirst
        on innocent blood, I have sent more souls than I can count into
        the infernal regions and I have spoken the words which bind my
        soul to my most wonderful patron. I now command a ship of demons
        and am well pleased. We shall become the scourge of the Inner
	Sea!"

                                         Captain Bloodheart
*DESCRIPTION_END
