ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The roar of rushing water, cascading down from an enormous opening high above
the floor of this lush grotto, reverberates deafeningly in this enclosed
chamber. Filled constantly to overflowing this small freshwater lake is
whipped to a frothy foam by the constant pounding of the invading river.
It churns and splashes up over the edges of this natural stone bowl, seeping
through the numerous rocky crevices and flowing out to join the sea. Slick
green moss covered rocks, large gray stone boulders, lacy ferns and water
spotted bushes crowd around the edges of the lake.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 2611
ITEM 1 411 ADJ1=202 ADJ2=152
ITEM 2 661 ADJ1=90
MONSTER_GROUP 102
IFVERB TOUCH 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You hand slides over the slick green moss preventing you from getting a firm hold on the rock.
  ECHO OTHERS %N tries to pick up a moss covered rock but %h fingers slip off the slick stone.
ENDIF
  IFVERB LISTEN -1
    ECHO PLAYER The pounding of the water makes it difficult to hear anything else at all.
    ECHO OTHERS %N cocks %h towards you, as if trying to not miss something you might have said.
  ENDIF
;
NUMBER 2612
NAME Cliff Stairs
JUNGLE
DAY_LIGHT
REGION 11
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Bits of loose rock and crumbling stone swirl around your head, buffeted by the
off-shore winds. The cliff face has been worn smooth by the constant breezes
as have the hand-carved steps which are now hardly more than faint
indentations. Broken twigs and blades of dried grass have been stuffed into
every available niche and crevice, home for the tiny birds peeking outwards
from their precarious nests.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT D 2610
EXIT U 2615
ITEM 0 406 ADJ1=415
MONSTER_GROUP 102
  IFVERB LISTEN -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You can hear the chirping and peeping of hungry chicks awaiting their parents return.
    ECHO OTHERS %N peers intently at one of the nests, smiling faintly to %iself.
  ENDIF
    IFVERB SNIFF -1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER As you take a deep breath you get a nose full of gritty dust.
      ECHO OTHERS %N suddenly begins sneezing and coughing!
    ENDIF
;
NUMBER 2615
NAME Cliff Edge
DAY_LIGHT
JUNGLE
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Buffeted by the ocean breezes and no longer protected by the sheltering cliffs,
you feel vunerable and exposed as you stand on the edge of the cliff
overlooking the sea at the tip of the island. Tall tufts of wild grass grow
almost sideways, flattened by the constant battering winds. A few stubby trees
claim a bit of earth, clinging forelornly to their precarious perch, their
limbs bent and arched inwards as if shielding themselves from the harsh
weather. A narrow trail meanders up a tall dune to the north.
*DESCRIPTION_END
