NUMBER 2616
NAME Dune
JUNGLE
DAY_LIGHT
REGION 11
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
As you edge away from the cliffs a verdant green wall of vegetation looms
in front of you, its expansion suddenly halted as if by some secret agreement.
Thin finger-like tendrils peeking out from the edge of the jungle and finding
nothing to attach themselves to, wind back around the dark green vines from
whence they sprouted. Rising up from the center of the jungle are jagged
mountains, the greater portion of their vast black forms shrouded in a thick
gray mist. A vine covered path leads deeper into the jungle to the northwest.
*DESCRIPTION_END
