*DESCRIPTION_START
Slithering up the wide fronds of an enormous tree fern, a large snake pauses
as it flicks out its tongue and stares at you. Apparently disinterested it
continues to wind its way upwards towards a white frog intent on a beetle
gripping the underside of a leaf just a few inches above its blinking eyes.
