CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
As you round the bend you can hear the roar of rushing water as well as feel a
slight dampness in the air. The ground is littered with small black veined
stones and larger deep gray boulders which seem to absorb the moisture,
glistening in the subdued light. Long sturdy vines wind their way between the
rocks eventually crawling over thick dark brown limbs which have fallen from
their massive hosts, left to decay and become one with the jungle floor. The
path weaves further around the bend to the northwest.
*DESCRIPTION_END
