DAY_LIGHT
JUNGLE
REGION 11
ITEM 9 693
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A shimmering cloud of mist hovers over the entire area constantly fed by the
river spewing forth over the giant boulders at the top of this magnificent
waterfall.Huge dark greyish black rocks, smoothed through the years by the
constant slapping of the liquid fingers, provide a slick surface for the watery
veil as it spills over them, tumbling and crashing downwards to vanish beneath
the rocks below. Ruffled ferns flourish in the many nooks and crevices, joined
by slender thin trunked trees and glossy dark green leafed shrubs. The path
slopes upwards to the north.
*DESCRIPTION_END
